From 33acbc89b6a2f8977a65f353fd163ebab6526c81 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Oliver Neukum <oneukum@suse.com>
Date: Tue, 24 Jun 2025 11:43:31 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Check for losing the race against dp_altmode_probe
Patch-mainline: Never (SUSE specific fix to preserve kABI)
References: CVE-2024-35790 bsc#1224712

This is an alternate fix for CVE-2024-35790
The upstream fix 165376f6b23e9a779850e750fb2eb06622e5a531
("usb: typec: altmodes/displayport: create sysfs nodes as driver's default device attribute group")
cannot be used in SLE12 because it requires a backport of
23b6904442d08b7dbed7622ed33b236d41a3aa8b
("driver core: add dev_groups to all drivers")
which in turn modifies struct device_driver. We absolutely
cannot touch that structure as it is embedded in read only memory
of all modules that implement a device driver. It would shred the kABI.

As an alternative, as we cannot use the infrastructure thus added,
we must deal with losing the race. Losing the race means that
typec_altmode_set_drvdata() returns NULL. If that happens,
we are just not yet ready to handle the syscall.
Just tell user space that that is the case.

Signed-off-by: Oliver Neukum <oneukum@suse.com>
---
 drivers/usb/typec/altmodes/displayport.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/typec/altmodes/displayport.c b/drivers/usb/typec/altmodes/displayport.c
index 3be9df443..6ed89760d 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/typec/altmodes/displayport.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/typec/altmodes/displayport.c
@@ -436,6 +436,9 @@ pin_assignment_store(struct device *dev, struct device_attribute *attr,
 	u32 conf;
 	int ret;
 
+	if (!dp)
+		return -EAGAIN;
+
 	ret = sysfs_match_string(pin_assignments, buf);
 	if (ret < 0)
 		return ret;
@@ -486,6 +489,9 @@ static ssize_t pin_assignment_show(struct device *dev,
 	u8 cur;
 	int i;
 
+	if (!dp)
+		return -EAGAIN;
+
 	mutex_lock(&dp->lock);
 
 	cur = get_count_order(DP_CONF_GET_PIN_ASSIGN(dp->data.conf));
-- 
